    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis for CFD hemolysis model — COU2 MRL 5",
    "description": "A variance-based (Sobol) global sensitivity analysis was performed over 2048 quasi-random LHS samples spanning eight uncertain inputs: blood viscosity (±15%), pump rotational speed (±3%), inlet flow rate (±5%), impeller blade clearance (±10 µm), outlet pressure boundary (±8%), hemolysis power-law exponent α (±12%), hemolysis power-law exponent β (±12%), and turbulent Schmidt number (±20%). The scalar hemolysis index (NIH) was the primary quantity of interest. First-order Sobol indices identified hemolysis exponent α (S₁ = 0.38) and blade clearance (S₁ = 0.27) as dominant contributors to NIH variance, together accounting for 65% of total output variance. Rotational speed contributed S₁ = 0.14. Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions (Sᵀ − S₁ < 0.04 for all factors). These results informed conservative uncertainty bands reported in the ValidationResult uncertainty quantification records.",
    "method": "Variance-based Sobol decomposition (Saltelli 2002 estimator)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "hemolysis power-law exponent alpha",
      "impeller blade clearance",
      "rotational speed"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 2048
  },
