    "name": "COU2: Cardiopulmonary bypass use — absolute hemolysis prediction (Class II, MRL 5)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) for a centrifugal blood pump operated during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is HIGH (model output directly informs device release decision without independent experimental confirmation of all operating points); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect hemolysis prediction could lead to patient harm). Model Risk Level 5.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute NIH values across the full operating envelope (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) for a Class II CPB centrifugal pump. Predictions are compared against FDA benchmark experimental data using a ±25% acceptance band on NIH.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
