      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: blood analog fluid and pump geometry scope",
      "description": "The CFD model is applicable only to Newtonian blood-analog fluids (glycerin-water mixture, dynamic viscosity 3.5 ± 0.5 mPa·s at 37°C) flowing through the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as defined in the 2012 FDA benchmark specification. The model is not applicable to non-Newtonian blood rheology, pulsatile flow waveforms, or pump geometries with impeller diameter deviating more than ±2 mm from the nominal 52 mm benchmark value. Patient-specific anatomical boundary conditions are outside scope."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
