      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, mg/100L) — is the regulatory standard metric for pump-induced hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance (2010 Guidance for Cardiopulmonary Bypass Oxygenators) and ISO 10993-4. Secondary QoIs include shear stress exposure time (SSET) and volume-averaged turbulent dissipation rate. All QoIs are directly linked to the clinical endpoint (patient red blood cell damage) through established mechanistic relationships documented in peer-reviewed literature.",
