      "rationale": "Validation activities were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump — the same geometry class as the device under assessment — under operating conditions spanning the full COU envelope (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). The validation fluid (glycerin-water blood analog) matches COU fluid properties within documented uncertainty. The hemolysis measurement protocol (ASTM F1841) used in validation experiments is identical to the protocol specified for device testing. No extrapolation beyond the validated operating envelope is required for COU2 predictions.",
