      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was verified for all simulations. Residuals for continuity, momentum, and scalar hemolysis equations were reduced to below 10⁻⁶ (normalized). Mass imbalance across all boundaries was below 0.01% of inlet mass flow rate. Temporal convergence for the unsteady (sliding mesh) simulations was confirmed by monitoring NIH over 10 impeller revolutions; cycle-to-cycle variation in NIH was below 0.3%. Double-precision arithmetic was used throughout.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
