      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was assessed through comparison of three turbulence closure models (SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and RSM) and two hemolysis power-law formulations (Giersiepen 1990 and Taskin 2012). The SST k-ω model with Giersiepen power-law produced the lowest E_n metric across all validation points and was selected as the primary model form. Model form uncertainty contribution to total NIH uncertainty was estimated at ±9% via the model ensemble spread, consistent with the Sobol analysis. The selected model form is documented and justified in the Model Description Document (MDD-COU2-v3).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
