      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "All model inputs were characterized with documented uncertainty distributions. Blood analog viscosity was measured by cone-and-plate viscometry (n=12 measurements, CV=2.1%). Pump geometry was digitized from CMM measurements of the physical impeller with dimensional tolerances of ±5 µm. Hemolysis power-law constants α and β were characterized from literature meta-analysis (n=8 independent studies) with 95% confidence intervals. Inlet boundary conditions were derived from PIV measurements. All input uncertainties were propagated through the Sobol analysis to quantify their contribution to output uncertainty.",
