      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The FDA interlaboratory hemolysis study used in validation comprised 5 independent laboratories, each performing hemolysis measurements at 5 operating points using ASTM F1841 protocol with fresh ovine blood (hematocrit 33±3%). Sample size per operating point ranged from n=6 to n=10 independent measurements. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation on NIH ranged from 14% to 22%, consistent with published interlaboratory variability for hemolysis testing. Sample representativeness of the COU blood analog was confirmed by viscosity matching.",
