      "rationale": "Equivalency between validation experiment input parameters and COU operating conditions was formally assessed using a parameter equivalency matrix. All eight primary input parameters (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, hematocrit, temperature, inlet pressure, outlet pressure, geometry) were compared between the validation dataset and COU specification. Six parameters were matched within ±5% of COU nominal values. Hematocrit equivalency was confirmed by sensitivity analysis showing NIH sensitivity to hematocrit is below 3% across the ±3% hematocrit range. No parameter required extrapolation beyond the validated range.",
